<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" size="6" color="#000066">The International School</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" size="6" color="#000066">of Moscow</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="4"><i>Chartered By The British Schools Foundation</i></font></div><div style="text-align: right;"><span style="text-align: left;"><br><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><br></span></div><div style="text-align: left;"><div style=""><div style=""><font face="arial">Dear Parents,</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">The health and safety of your children is our top priority. In addition to our daily precautions, we aim to always keep our parents well informed of anything that comes to our attention which may affect your children.</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">&nbsp;</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">Today, I am writing to inform you that there has been a confirmed case of scarlet fever in one of our Year 2 classes. Scarlet fever is a contagious, bacterial illness that mainly affects children. It is spread by airborne droplets, through contact or from sharing towels/bed linens, etc. Symptoms initially include: a sore throat, headache, high temperature, flushed cheeks and a swollen tongue. A day or two later, the characteristic pinkish rash of scarlet fever appears which may be itchy and feel like sandpaper to touch. Please seek immediate medical advice and advise the school promptly if your child is unwell with any of the above symptoms.</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">&nbsp;</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">At school, we are taking all precautions necessary including:</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">&nbsp;</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">●&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Maintaining the usual strict student hygiene routines to prevent spread of illness.</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">●&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Overnight a deep-clean of the Campus will take place. This includes full cleaning and disinfection of surfaces, door handles, stair railings, toys, classrooms, bathrooms, common areas, and food-related areas.</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">●&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The nurse will check the temperature and wellbeing of all pupils through the day. Children displaying symptoms will see the nurse for further examination and if necessary, parents will be contacted to collect them.</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">&nbsp;</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">If you believe your child has scarlet fever, please seek medical treatment, follow safety procedures at home and keep them away from school until they have recovered from the illness.</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">&nbsp;</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">For further information about scarlet fever, please see the link below:</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial"><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/scarlet-fever/pages/introduction.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/scarlet-fever/pages/introduction.aspx</a></font></div><div style=""><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">Warm regards,</font></div><div style=""><br></div><div style=""><span id="docs-internal-guid-beb5747f-1108-886c-3a7d-aaa2068d572a"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Cambria; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/tVIXwgIF8uVdGh2jHxAjQMAYmsK5mahI1WGdpCYfFCHg1LamgN4UAoS2Oc6U2AEHZfqaylxQpZaDpDjMGB2w0Z9YSVFJF7W2lAGwVOrR7C6zz4crgpdnLsANjzfG--hrUUE6VP5y" width="68" height="42" style="border: none; transform: rotate(0.00rad); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad);"></span></span></div><div style=""><span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Cambria; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br></span></span></div><div style=""><font face="arial">Justin Noack</font></div><div style=""><font face="arial">Head of ISM Lower Campus</font></div></div></div></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">The International School of Moscow<br></span><i style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600"><b>World Class Education</b></font></i></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">__________________________________________________________</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">{!User.School_List_Email_Footer__c}</font><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</font></div>]]></td>
